&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Senior Product Designer to help shape the future of Datadog’s design ecosystem across our suite of products and platform experiences. You’ll play a key role in crafting cohesive, user-centered solutions that empower customers to visualize, monitor, and optimize their systems with confidence.&amp;nbsp;You’ll collaborate closely with engineers, product managers, and designers across multiple teams to simplify complex workflows and create elegant, scalable design solutions that span our 70+ products.At Datadog, we value the relationships and creativity that thrive in our office culture. We operate as a hybrid workplace to help our Datadogs build a work-life harmony that fits them best.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;At Datadog, we place value in our office culture - the relationships and collaboration it builds and the creativity it brings to the table. We operate as a hybrid workplace to ensure our Datadogs can create a work-life harmony that best fits them.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead end-to-end design work, from user research and concepting to high-fidelity prototyping and production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional partners (PMs, engineers, and fellow designers) to ensure we build the right experiences for our customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to and evolve Datadog’s cohesive design language and overall UX vision across products and platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advocate for user needs through thoughtful design decisions and clear communication with stakeholders at all levels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop deep expertise in your focus area while sharing knowledge and best practices across the broader design team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion design thinking and promote a high-quality, consistent user experience across the entire Datadog ecosystem.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have 7+ years of experience in digital product design, preferably within SaaS or other complex systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your portfolio demonstrates end-to-end design execution with measurable impact and high-quality user experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are an excellent communicator, able to clearly articulate design rationale and collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re proficient in modern design and prototyping tools (e.g., Figma, Sketch, Framer, InVision, Principle).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You think in systems and are comfortable working within and contributing to component-based design patterns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You value feedback and collaboration, helping to elevate both your own work and that of your peers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Datadog values people from all walks of life. We understand not everyone will meet all the above qualifications on day one. That&#39;s okay. If you’re passionate about technology and want to grow your skills, we encourage you to apply.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
